cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the task of transcription of handwritten text on images using machine learning, specifically multi-dimensional recurrent neural networks (MDRNN) with connectionist temporal classification (CTC). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves image processing and computer vision, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the properties and design of cells in MDRNNs, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper applies the developed cells to handwriting recognition, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
